children.name: get_version
children.comment: Return a PEP 440-compliant version number from VERSION.

children.name: update
children.comment: Extend rather than replace existing key lists.

children.name: lists
children.comment: Yield (key, list) pairs.

children.name: patch_cache_control
children.comment:
Patch the Cache-Control header by adding all keyword arguments to it.
The transformation is as follows:

* All keyword parameter names are turned to lowercase, and underscores
  are converted to hyphens.
* If the value of a parameter is True (exactly True, not just a
  true value), only the parameter name is added to the header.
* All other parameters are added with their value, after applying
  str() to it.

children.name: format_html
children.comment:
Similar to str.format, but pass all arguments through conditional_escape(),
and call mark_safe() on the result. This function should be used instead
of str.format or % interpolation to build up small HTML fragments.

children.name: get_bytes_from_wsgi
children.comment:
Get a value from the WSGI environ dictionary as bytes.

key and default should be strings.

children.name: _get_response
children.comment:
Resolve and call the view, then apply view, exception, and
template_response middleware. This method is everything that happens
inside the request/response middleware.

children.name: copy
children.comment: Return a mutable copy of this object.

children.name: _load_post_and_files
children.comment: Populate self._post and self._files if the content-type is a form type

children.name: build_absolute_uri
children.comment:
Build an absolute URI from the location and the variables available in
this request. If no ``location`` is specified, build the absolute URI
using request.get_full_path(). If the location is absolute, convert it
to an RFC 3987 compliant URI and return it. If location is relative or
is scheme-relative (i.e., ``//example.com/``), urljoin() it to a base
URL constructed from the request variables.

children.name: make_bytes
children.comment: Turn a value into a bytestring encoded in the output charset.

children.name: process_request
children.comment:
Check for denied User-Agents and rewrite the URL based on
settings.APPEND_SLASH and settings.PREPEND_WWW

children.name: process_response
children.comment:
When the status code of the response is 404, it may redirect to a path
with an appended slash if should_redirect_with_slash() returns True.

children.name: process_response
children.comment:
If request.session was modified, or if the configuration is to save the
session every time, save the changes and set a session cookie or delete
the session cookie if the session has been emptied.

children.name: process_response
children.comment:
Update the storage backend (i.e., save the messages).

Raise ValueError if not all messages could be stored and DEBUG is True.

children.name: get_queryset
children.comment:
Return a new QuerySet object. Subclasses can override this method to
customize the behavior of the Manager.

children.name: count
children.comment:
Perform a SELECT COUNT() and return the number of records as an
integer.

If the QuerySet is already fully cached, return the length of the
cached results set to avoid multiple SELECT COUNT(*) calls.

children.name: filter
children.comment:
Return a new QuerySet instance with the args ANDed to the existing
set.

children.name: render
children.comment:
Return an HttpResponse whose content is filled with the result of calling
django.template.loader.render_to_string() with the passed arguments.

children.name: static
children.comment:
Given a relative path to a static asset, return the absolute path to the
asset.
